insert into venue values (NULL,'Founded in December 2004 by art historian and curator Dr. Ziba Ardalan, Parasol unit foundation for contemporary art is a not-for-profit art institution that operates purely for the public benefit. Central to the Parasol unit philosophy is a total commitment to artists and their creative endeavour, an attitude which leads to a singular relationship developing between each exhibiting artist and the foundation.','Parasol Unit',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'14 Wharf Road N1 7RW London',NULL,0,51.5302681,'14 Wharf Road N1 7RW London',-0.094909199999961,'Tuesday - Saturday : 10:00 - 18:00, Sunday : 12:00 - 17:00, or by appointment',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'www.parasol-unit.org');
insert into venue values (NULL,'Edge of Arabia was founded by British artist Stephen Stapleton, with Saudi artists Ahmed Mater and Abdulnasser Gharem in the mountains of South Western Saudi Arabia, in March 2003. What began as an unlikely friendship and artistic collaboration is now an internationally recognised platform for dialogue and exchange between the Middle East and western world. As a non-profit social enterprise, Edge of Arabia is committed to reaching new audiences and improving understanding through free exhibitions, publications and public programming. To date, Edge of Arabia  has welcomed 300,000 visitors to its exhibitions, distributed over 50,000 books & catalogues worldwide and reached a wider audience of over 10,000,000 through a dedicated communications campaign.','Edge of Arabia',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'40 Elcho Street SW11 4AU London',NULL,0,51.4797429,'40 Elcho Street SW11 4AU London',-0.168533099999991,'Tuesday - Saturday : 10:00 - 18:00',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'edgeofarabia.com');
insert into venue values (NULL,'38b is an occasional series of exhibitions and events programmed by Luke Drozd and Eva Rowson in their flat at 38b Peckham Rye.

38b started in 2010 out of a desire to create a space for ourselves and artists we admire to show new work and try out ideas, and the most immediate, cheapest way to do this was to transform our living room into an exhibition space. Some artists have preferred to strip the room of any trace of our inhabitancy and use it as a white walled gallery space and others have enjoyed playing with the domesticity of the setting.

We continue to host exhibitions at 38b Peckham Rye but as we also start to programme projects beyond the flat our intentions remain the same - to provide an accessible and uncostly space for artists to experiment and exhibit.','38b ',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'38b Peckham Rye SE15 4JR London',NULL,0,51.4655545,'38b Peckham Rye SE15 4JR London',-0.0667095999999674,'Saturday - Sunday :11:00 - 18:00, Monday - Friday :  by appointment only',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'www.38bprojects.com');
