insert into venue values (NULL,'Curious Duke Gallery may have began in September 2011 as a pop up, in addition to the online gallery, but CDG now stands as a fully fledged \'anti-gallery\'. Curious Duke Gallery is currently London\'s leading urban and contemporary art space for emerging artists. Founded by 27 year old Eleni Duke, dubbed the Duchess of Whitecross Street, the business has grown exponentially to great acclaim having won second place in Smarta 100 Micro Business Awards 2013. But not only that, Curious Duke Gallery is the only space in London to specialise in urban and contemporary art works from new artists. You will find obscure methods of art from laser cut vintage saws depicting childhood scenes, to bic biro drawings on antique documents nestling between bright mixed media paintings of native american inspired women. ','Curious Duke Gallery',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'173 Whitecross Street EC1Y 8JT London',NULL,0,51.5236357,'173 Whitecross Street EC1Y 8JT London',-0.0934994000000415,'Monday - Friday : 11:30 -18:30, Saturday : 12:00 - 16:00, Sunday : by appointment',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'curiousdukegallery.com');
insert into venue values (NULL,'Our distinguished gallery space at number 30 Cork Street was once home to the Peggy Guggenheim Gallery. Peggy Guggenheim was recognised as one of the most important names in the Art world through the Guggenheim Collection. The opening of the Guggenheim “Jeune” Gallery in January 1938 at 30 Cork Street, launched her career; a career that would decidedly alter the course of post-war Art. It was here where Wassily Kandinsky had his first ever London show.
We are in the heart of the Art district in Mayfair, minutes walk from the Royal Academy of Arts. Cork Street is known as the “Mecca” of Art galleries and is home to some of the most influential dealers of the world. Many major Art dealers have shown in Cork Street at some point or other. With Bond Street and the world’s most renowned auction houses – Sotheby’s and Christie’s just around the corner, it is the perfect breeding ground for Art talent, and Art trade.
At present, Cork Street is undergoing major redevelopments due for completion in 2017, which will see this street expand and welcome even more galleries and dealers.
We want to provide potential buyers with the most recent, comprehensive information on art, artists and their current and speculated position in the market. In order to achieve this, it is important to have a presence; a gallery, where works can be shown and living artists can be represented. This is done through Dadiani Fine Art dealership.
As well as numerous exhibitions, we host cultural events, talks and evenings dedicated to introduce and acquaint the  public to our artists and more.','Dadiani Fine Art',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'30 Cork Street W1S 3NG London',NULL,0,51.5106077,'30 Cork Street W1S 3NG London',-0.141254600000025,'Monday - Friday : 11:00 - 18:00, Saturday : 11:00 - 15:00',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'dadianifineart.com');
