insert into venue values (NULL,'Jack Bell Gallery opened in London in 2010. The focus of the gallery is to exhibit, represent and champion contemporary artists from around the world. The program includes ten exhibitions every year as well as art fairs in London, New York and Miami. Gallery artists have been included in important exhibitions at the Venice Biennale, Brooklyn Museum, New York, Grand Palais, Paris, Guggenheim, Bilbao, Centre Pompidou, Paris, Salon 94, New York, Saatchi Gallery, London, and Studio Museum, New York, among others.','Jack Bell Gallery',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'13 Masons Yard SW1Y 6BU London',NULL,0,51.5076125,'13 Masons Yard SW1Y 6BU London',-0.137240799999972,'Tuesday - Friday : 11:00 - 18:00, Saturday : 12:00 - 16:00',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'www.jackbellgallery.com');
insert into venue values (NULL,'jaggedart is known for its unique and very definite style. Since its inception ten years ago the gallery has become renowned for showcasing beautiful, quirky yet sophisticated works of art.

The gallery promotes up and coming artists through a varied programme of exhibitions which include painting, photography, works on paper and 3 dimensional pieces. Our programme varies between themed shows and solo exhibitions. Artists are invited to use the space in a dynamic way, creating site specific installations in the gallery and large shop frontage.

The artists\' intense involvement with the creative process, always evident, results in remarkably stimulating pieces.

Although they work in traditional media, jaggedart artists use materials in innovative ways: books, maps, audio tape, cement, textiles and embroidery thread are examples. The works offer a poetic perspective on the familiar, a new life for the discarded, re-discovering a forgotten elegance.','JaggedArt',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'28 A Devonshire Street W1G 6PS London',NULL,0,51.5209336,'28 A Devonshire Street W1G 6PS London',-0.151659500000051,'Wedesday - Friday : 11:00 - 18:00, Saturday : 11:00 - 14:00, or by appointment',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'www.jaggedart.com');
insert into venue values (NULL,'James Hyman Fine Art Limited was founded in 1999 and aspires to deal in museum quality fine art of art historical significance in particular by twentieth century British Artists. The gallery specialises in modern British drawings, paintings, and sculpture, especially by the School of London. The gallery represents many artists and estates as well as having a deep inventory of paintings and drawings. Exhibitions have included represented gallery artists as well as high profile solo exhibitions of Francis Bacon, Lucian Freud, Pablo Picasso and Bridget Riley.','James Hyman Gallery',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'16 Savile Row W1S 3PL London',NULL,0,51.5112592,'16 Savile Row W1S 3PL London',-0.14037780000001,'Monday - Friday : 10:00 - 18:00 ',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'www.jameshymangallery.com');
