insert into venue values (NULL,'Our mission is to support community renewal in East London by delivering Arts and Creative Services through our financially sustainable social enterprise model.

Bow Arts was established in 1994 by Marcel Baettig with the kind support of Marc Schimmel, the owner of our Bow Road premises and a valued supporter of the arts. This first site, formed of two adjacent buildings, quickly established itself as a thriving artist studios supporting over 100 working artists.

In 1995 the Trust became a registered arts and education charity, then by 1998, with the further support of Marc Schimmel alongside an Arts Council England grant, we were able to build the Nunnery Gallery, a contemporary art gallery housed at the heart of our Bow Road site.

At the same time we established our now, award winning, schools education programme. The education programme, now working with over 80 schools, offers employment and training opportunities for professional artists in these schools. The artists help young people access education, improve their attainment and learn valuable creative skills.

At present, Bow Arts manages eight different Studio sites across London and we are developing more. We also operate a Live Work scheme throughout Bow, this provides housing for practising artists who have an interest in community work, one of our sites includes the iconic  Balfron Tower. Our workspace schemes support over 500 artists with affordable safe spaces to work and grow.','Nunnery Gallery',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'181 Bow Road E3 2SJ London',NULL,0,51.5291009,'181 Bow Road E3 2SJ London',-0.0168888000000607,'Tuesday - Sunday : 10:00 - 16:00',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'bowarts.org');
insert into venue values (NULL,'Founded in 1979, October Gallery, in central London, exhibits innovative, contemporary art from around the world. For over 35 years, October Gallery has pioneered the development of the Transvangarde - the trans-cultural avant-garde.','October Gallery',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'24 Old Gloucester Street WC1N 3AL London',NULL,0,51.520692,'24 Old Gloucester Street WC1N 3AL London',-0.121730500000012,'Tuesday - Saturday : 12:30 - 17:30 ',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'www.octobergallery.co.uk');
