insert into venue values (NULL,'Pi Artworks Istanbul/London was founded by Yesim Turanli in 1998 in Istanbul.
By the early 2000’s Pi Artworks was one of a small number of galleries that was successfully introducing young Turkish artists into the market. In 2008 the gallery led the way by being the first of over ten galleries to relocate to Istanbul’s Tophane district. From 2009 onwards Pi Artworks has grown to include international artists, promoting them heavily to its local market. In 2011 the gallery expanded once more by opening another branch in Istanbul, and moving its headquarters to Misir Apt. building, an historic building at the heart of Istanbul’s contemporary art district. In October 2013 it became the first Turkish commercial gallery to expand into the UK when Pi Artworks London opened on 55 Eastcastle Street, in the heart of bustling Fitzrovia. ','Pi Artworks',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'55 Eastcastle Street W1W 8EG London',NULL,0,51.5164124,'55 Eastcastle Street W1W 8EG London',-0.138135700000021,'Monday - Friday : 10:00 - 18:00,  Saturday: 11:00 - 18:00',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'www.piartworks.com');
insert into venue values (NULL,'Piano Nobile specialises in 20th-century works of art ranging from international, modern British and postwar paintings, drawings and sculpture. The gallery\'s inventory extends from carefully sourced impressionist, post-impressionist, futurist, constructervist and expressionist stock to post-war abstract expressionism and the avant-garde, all of the highest quality, by acclaimed and celebrated artists of these periods. Our focus on quality of works available on the market, at a given price point, also extends to the services and advice we offer to our clients, both established collectors and those involved in a wider range of art related activities. The gallery also represents a select stable of contemporary, internationally based artists who draw on traditional forms of art and apply them in a contemporary context, using figurative representation in an abstract sense, often as much conceptual as figurative. These artists are established, many with international reputations commercially and in the museum world.','Piano Nobile',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'129 Portland Road W11 4LW London',NULL,0,51.510022,'129 Portland Road W11 4LW London',-0.210566299999982,'Monday - Friday : 10:00 - 18:00, Saturday : 11:00 - 16:00pm, or by appointment',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'http://www.piano-nobile.com');
