insert into venue values (NULL,'Established in 1998, Sarah Myerscough Gallery promotes formal and aesthetic innovations within the contemporary visual arts by breaking down boundaries between fine art, craft, design and architecture. As a multidisciplinary platform, the gallery supports and promotes quality of process and practice across disciplines, with a particular focus on woodwork and more recently digital art. The gallery represents emerging and established international artists and designers exhibiting in major galleries and museums, while it continues to establish its presence at art fairs around the world, PAD London, Art Paris, Design Miami/Basel, Design Miami, Art Geneve, SALON New York, SOFA Chicago, Design Days Dubai and Craft Trend Seoul.','Sarah Myerscough Fine Art',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'15-16 Brooks Mews W1K 4DS London',NULL,0,51.5123272,'15-16 Brooks Mews W1K 4DS London',-0.146488099999942,'Monday - Friday : 10:00 - 18:00, Saturday : 12:00 - 15:00',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'www.sarahmyerscough.com');
insert into venue values (NULL,'Schwartz Gallery is located on White Post Lane located in the London Borough of Tower Hamlets next to Victoria Park in the heart of London’s Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park.It was founded in April 2008 by artist-curators Patrick Michalopoulos and Ismail Erbil and directed by them jointly until January 2016. Questioning exhibition and display formats Schwartz Gallery became an important platform and forum for emerging contemporary art practice and debate in East London and beyond.  ','Schwartz Gallery',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'92 White Post Lane E9 5EN London',NULL,0,51.5429561,'92 White Post Lane E9 5EN London',-0.0231367000000091,'Thursday - Saturday : 13:00 – 18:00, or by appointment',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'www.schwartzgallery.co.uk');
