insert into venue values (NULL,'Serena Morton was born and raised in London and came from an artistic background.

For the first ten years of her career she worked in fashion and media and then made the next logical move into the art world.

Serena moved to Christie’s Auction House, King Street, London in 1994-1998 and worked in the Print Department, Modern British and Post-War and Contemporary British Paintings and Sculpture which inspired her to curate and produce contemporary art exhibitions.

Serena Morton was among the first London curators of pop-up exhibitions. From 2006- 2011, she launched and directed three ‘West End’ London art galleries in Berners Street (Fitzrovia), Dover Street (Mayfair).

From 2006-2008 Morton launched, directed and curated Ronnie Wood’s Scream Gallery in Mayfair.

In 2008 Morton started her own art gallery business. In 2010 she teamed up with music manager Raye Cosbert (Metropolis Music/Amy Winehouse manager) to open the concept art gallery Morton Metropolis.

She followed this with her own gallery, Agent Morton on Dover Street. After a year curating and establishing a contemporary art exhibition for the private members club Home House on Portman Square, she built and launched Serena Morton gallery at Canalside, 385 Ladbroke Grove. In November 2014 she consolidated her position in the area by opening her second space, at 343 Ladbroke Grove.

Serena Morton’s exhibitions have won critical approval and have a proven track record of identifying emerging artists. Serena Morton supports and advises artists and collectors on all areas of the art world.','Serena Morton',2,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'343 Ladbroke Grove W10 6HA London',NULL,0,51.5232443,'343 Ladbroke Grove W10 6HA London',-0.213738299999932,'Monday - Friday : 10:00 - 18:00, Saturday :11:00 - 16:00',CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,'www.serenamorton.com');
